<oXygen:ReusableComponent id="ReusableComponent_qfp_mkf_2t">
    <oXygen:ComponentDescription></oXygen:ComponentDescription>
    <oXygen:ComponentDefinition><conbody id="conbody_sfp_mkf_2t"><p>The <i>Assignment Roles</i> related list on an Item Class record, with the <b>Is Subscription</b> checkbox enabled, allows staff users to manually configure assignments:<ul id="ul_nqw_p4l_ss"><li><b>Receives Email Communications</b>-Check the <b>Receives Email Communications</b> checkbox to allow the customer to receive emails related to renewal notices, subscription logs, subscription amendments, and any other Admin modifications to their subscription. </li><li><p><b>Is Primary</b>-When a customer is assigned to a subscription with <b>Is Primary</b> checked, the customer can modify their subscription in the <b>Community Portal</b>.</p></li><li><b>Is Default</b>-When an Assignment Role is not selected, the customer is auto-assigned a <b>Default</b> role that will allow the assignee to view their subscription in the <b>Community Portal</b>.</li><li><b>Is Active</b>-The <b>Is Active</b> checkbox must be enabled in order for the items related to the subscription based Item Class to display in the <b>Community Portal</b>.</li></ul></p><p>At a minimum, a subscription based Item Class must have at least one Assignment Role with the <b>Is Default</b> and <b>Is Active</b> checkboxes enabled. If the Assignment is not the same as the Contact on the Sales Order, users must navigate to the Sales Order record to identify the Contact purchasing the subscription. All Assignments can view the subscriptions that are assigned to them. In order to allow the customer full access to subscription management in the <b>Community Portal</b>, enable <b>Receives Email Communications</b>, <b>Is Primary</b>, and <b>Is Active</b>.</p><p>After setting Assignment Roles: <ul id="ul_nhx_2vl_ss"><li><xref href="creating_item_classes.dita#task_zdr_yqj_gs">Create an Item Class for Subscriptions and Set Assignment Roles</xref></li></ul></p></conbody></oXygen:ComponentDefinition>
</oXygen:ReusableComponent>